02:26.687 --> 02:35.787
♪♪

02:35.823 --> 02:44.923
♪♪

02:44.959 --> 02:54.058
♪♪

02:54.284 --> 02:55.658
DE MOLAY: Draper.

02:55.804 --> 03:00.535
♪♪

03:00.602 --> 03:02.025
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

03:02.061 --> 03:10.201
♪♪

03:10.237 --> 03:18.419
♪♪

03:18.455 --> 03:26.595
♪♪

03:27.018 --> 03:29.310
Ulric.
Brothers, help.

03:29.365 --> 03:34.937
♪♪

03:34.973 --> 03:40.569
♪♪

03:41.095 --> 03:43.530
You!

03:43.694 --> 03:46.066
You should have let me
go with them!

03:46.144 --> 03:50.371
Then I'd be burying you,
as well.

03:50.470 --> 03:52.916
Step back, Initiate.

03:53.209 --> 03:57.379
Or I promise,
you will join them presently.

03:57.733 --> 03:58.964
[SIGHS]

03:59.000 --> 04:01.779
♪♪

04:01.815 --> 04:06.777
Subtitles by explosiveskull

04:11.681 --> 04:13.189
[DOOR OPENS]

04:13.225 --> 04:19.070
♪♪

04:19.310 --> 04:21.421
DE NOGARET:
My Lord. Your Grace.

04:21.488 --> 04:23.204
I present Sir Gawain.

04:23.756 --> 04:26.370
Is this the man you've been
prattling on about?

04:26.617 --> 04:28.164
Former Templar?

04:28.353 --> 04:29.249
It is.

04:29.285 --> 04:34.963
♪♪

04:35.399 --> 04:37.527
I too would gauge
the man's worth.

04:38.297 --> 04:39.971
I will send for you.

04:40.133 --> 04:43.267
Come.
We have pressing matters.

04:43.571 --> 04:45.333
De Nogaret.

04:45.369 --> 04:46.870
My Lord.

04:49.560 --> 04:51.062
Did you speak
to our friend?

04:51.098 --> 04:53.523
I was just on my way there now,
Your Majesty.

04:53.560 --> 04:56.271
Good.
Be gentle with him.

04:56.310 --> 04:59.022
He doesn't have the stomach
that you and I have.

05:02.091 --> 05:04.099
It appears
Gawain has forgotten

05:04.135 --> 05:07.102
how to properly greet his king,
De Nogaret.

05:07.812 --> 05:10.008
On your knees.

05:10.062 --> 05:12.316
Apologies,
Your Majesty.

05:12.352 --> 05:13.567
[GROANS]

05:13.775 --> 05:22.499
♪♪

05:22.666 --> 05:27.797
De Nogaret thinks you should
be allowed back in my employ.

05:28.059 --> 05:29.769
Why?

05:30.305 --> 05:33.147
Because I can help you kill
Landry and destroy the Templars.

05:33.183 --> 05:36.483
A half man
against Landry.

05:36.683 --> 05:41.653
You talk of some great warrior,
and this is what greets me?

05:41.697 --> 05:44.867
A former Templar incapable
of standing erect.

05:47.980 --> 05:52.032
Perhaps I need to counsel you,
Counselor.

05:52.068 --> 05:56.266
♪♪

05:56.426 --> 05:58.082
I told you
to present well.

05:58.182 --> 06:01.441
This is as well
as I present...

06:01.477 --> 06:04.987
absent means
to fix certain afflictions.

06:05.132 --> 06:14.713
♪♪

06:14.749 --> 06:16.090
[SIGHS]

06:16.763 --> 06:22.817
♪♪

06:22.853 --> 06:28.866
♪♪

06:28.984 --> 06:31.020
PRINCE LOUIS:
Margaret. My love.

06:31.091 --> 06:33.808
[LAUGHS]

06:34.055 --> 06:36.891
Ohh.

06:40.391 --> 06:41.972
I-I didn't expect you
for another...

06:42.008 --> 06:43.708
I'm so sorry
about your mother.

06:43.744 --> 06:46.024
- I tried to get here sooner, but...
- Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh, shh, shh.

06:46.060 --> 06:47.484
No more of this.

06:47.683 --> 06:48.923
You're here now.

06:48.984 --> 06:51.742
[SIGHS]

06:52.177 --> 06:57.898
♪♪

06:58.045 --> 06:59.315
[SIGHS]

06:59.394 --> 07:02.756
Should we trade such intimacies
in front of strangers?

07:02.792 --> 07:04.302
[LAUGHS]

07:04.338 --> 07:05.796
They are not strangers.

07:05.860 --> 07:09.014
They are
my most loyal retainers,

07:09.050 --> 07:10.558
and they've witnessed
more indiscretions

07:10.594 --> 07:13.128
than you and I combined,
I'll wager.

07:13.285 --> 07:17.503
And may I ask where you
and your retainers are off to?

07:17.752 --> 07:20.458
More of my father's chores
to attend to.

07:20.494 --> 07:23.385
Such is the price to be
the next king of France.

07:23.476 --> 07:25.025
Might it wait?

07:25.097 --> 07:28.090
We have so much...
catching up to do.

07:28.161 --> 07:30.002
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

07:30.409 --> 07:34.517
I won't be long, and then
we can catch up properly.

07:35.422 --> 07:36.887
Hmm?

07:36.946 --> 07:38.020
Get yourself settled.

07:38.090 --> 07:40.203
I've arranged for you
to have my mother's old room.

07:40.261 --> 07:43.311
A queen's chamber
for my future queen.

07:43.597 --> 07:45.124
As you wish.

07:45.188 --> 07:47.488
But please do hurry.

07:47.782 --> 07:56.292
♪♪

07:58.377 --> 07:59.902
PRINCESS ISABELLA:
And off they go.

07:59.972 --> 08:02.103
- Isabella!
- [LAUGHS]

08:02.170 --> 08:03.531
Ohh.

08:03.586 --> 08:06.184
Men playing at
doing important things

08:06.220 --> 08:08.549
and leaving us to clean up
after their messes

08:08.585 --> 08:10.347
and suffer the consequences.

08:10.383 --> 08:13.099
I'm quite sure I don't know
what you're on about.

08:13.135 --> 08:16.270
Louis must prepare himself
to one day sit upon the throne.

08:16.422 --> 08:19.261
I can't even imagine the
pressures that weigh upon him.

08:19.297 --> 08:22.973
My brother is not the only one
with royal obligations.

08:23.390 --> 08:27.107
You need not worry about
anything from now on, Isabella.

08:27.378 --> 08:29.414
When the time does come
for Louis to be king

08:29.485 --> 08:32.129
and I am made
queen of France,

08:32.418 --> 08:35.466
I will make sure
you are well looked after.

08:35.624 --> 08:37.226
We are sisters now.

08:37.275 --> 08:39.783
And there will always be a place
for you in this house.

08:40.006 --> 08:41.765
I promise.

08:41.801 --> 08:51.400
♪♪

08:51.436 --> 08:53.648
[WATER SPLASHES]

08:56.745 --> 08:59.003
Now, what should I
call you?

08:59.412 --> 09:02.363
"Father" doesn't seem
appropriate.

09:02.399 --> 09:04.186
It was appropriate enough
last night.

09:04.261 --> 09:05.804
[CHUCKLES]

09:07.264 --> 09:08.567
[DOOR OPENS]

09:08.633 --> 09:10.135
Not now!
I'm busy!

09:13.044 --> 09:16.814
De Nogaret.
What do you want?

09:16.890 --> 09:21.358
Sorry to interrupt communion
with your... friend, Raymond,

09:21.464 --> 09:24.509
but King Philip has requested
your presence, hmm?

09:27.242 --> 09:29.119
- Aah!
- [GASPS]

09:31.591 --> 09:33.718
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

09:38.153 --> 09:41.204
And I would not keep
His Majesty waiting.

09:41.561 --> 09:43.646
Your Excellency.

09:50.587 --> 09:54.388
♪♪

09:54.458 --> 09:55.757
[LANDRY EXHALES SHARPLY]

09:55.926 --> 10:05.192
♪♪

10:05.228 --> 10:14.363
♪♪

10:14.449 --> 10:16.957
I'm sorry, Draper.

10:17.033 --> 10:20.335
You amongst us all
walked the righteous path

10:20.371 --> 10:22.879
with courage and admiration.

10:22.915 --> 10:27.232
♪♪

10:27.305 --> 10:32.232
I promise you, brother,
your death will not be in vain.

10:32.550 --> 10:38.688
♪♪

10:38.724 --> 10:44.862
♪♪

10:44.898 --> 10:49.033
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

10:49.069 --> 10:52.412
♪♪

10:52.562 --> 10:54.554
RHONE: Landry?

10:54.635 --> 10:57.685
What are you doing?

10:57.870 --> 11:00.344
It is our sacred duty
to purify the dead

11:00.380 --> 11:02.215
before giving them
a proper burial.

11:07.414 --> 11:08.832
Here.

11:10.552 --> 11:12.804
[WATER SPLASHING]

11:13.834 --> 11:15.210
Take it.

11:23.789 --> 11:25.419
RHONE: Before I joined
the Order, my, uh...

11:25.455 --> 11:27.338
my grandmother
had just passed.

11:27.738 --> 11:30.207
When she died,
it, uh, felt as if

11:30.243 --> 11:32.871
she'd gone for a long walk
and never come back.

11:37.137 --> 11:39.756
[CRYING] This doesn't
feel like that, does it?

11:39.957 --> 11:43.011
Nor should it.

11:43.230 --> 11:46.180
These men didn't die.

11:46.216 --> 11:47.739
They were executed.

11:47.814 --> 11:50.876
Do you think those who did
these horrible things

11:50.936 --> 11:54.654
can ever be forgiven
by God?

11:55.138 --> 11:59.362
God is within His rights
to abandon a sinner.

11:59.398 --> 12:09.373
♪♪

12:09.409 --> 12:19.140
♪♪

12:19.232 --> 12:21.657
[GRUNTING]

12:21.882 --> 12:30.329
♪♪

12:30.461 --> 12:31.670
DE NOGARET:
Your Majesty.

12:33.477 --> 12:35.235
Your Majesty.

12:35.294 --> 12:37.887
Archbishop
Raymond de Goth.

12:38.025 --> 12:45.873
♪♪

12:45.909 --> 12:53.521
♪♪

12:53.578 --> 12:57.047
[WOOD CLATTERS,
FLAMES CRACKLING]

12:57.278 --> 12:59.197
A bit chilly in here.

13:01.561 --> 13:06.419
Archbishop, I am afraid
I have some terrible news.

13:06.496 --> 13:08.040
The pope is dead.

13:13.850 --> 13:15.310
When did this happen?

13:15.403 --> 13:17.369
Last night.

13:17.815 --> 13:18.839
In his sleep.

13:18.891 --> 13:21.561
Apologies, Your Majesty,
but I must make arrangements

13:21.597 --> 13:24.105
to accompany his body
back to Rome.

13:24.256 --> 13:26.431
KING PHILIP:
Raymond, stop.

13:26.663 --> 13:31.925
♪♪

13:31.961 --> 13:35.303
Listen to me.

13:35.414 --> 13:37.068
In light of this tragedy,

13:37.153 --> 13:42.164
I believe there might be a way
for us both to benefit.

13:43.063 --> 13:44.128
Your Majesty?

13:44.164 --> 13:47.214
The Italians have had
their reign as pope long enough.

13:47.292 --> 13:51.770
There now exists a majority
of French Cardinals

13:51.806 --> 13:52.940
in the conclave.

13:53.019 --> 13:56.612
I would have someone of...

13:56.822 --> 14:02.083
like mind
to assume St. Peter's mantle.

14:02.119 --> 14:05.930
And that someone...

14:06.020 --> 14:07.568
is you.

14:07.792 --> 14:11.440
♪♪

14:16.165 --> 14:19.251
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

14:20.961 --> 14:23.298
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

14:23.718 --> 14:25.058
Can I help you?

14:25.094 --> 14:26.977
Good day, sir.

14:27.201 --> 14:29.298
My Templar brothers and I
were wondering

14:29.334 --> 14:31.567
if we might trouble you
for some water.

14:31.641 --> 14:33.059
Come in.

14:41.631 --> 14:44.204
Are your wife
and son home?

14:44.442 --> 14:45.332
My wife?

14:45.368 --> 14:46.169
[WATER POURING]

14:46.240 --> 14:48.207
Yes.

14:48.375 --> 14:49.841
Lydia.

14:49.956 --> 14:51.640
She's at the market.

14:51.702 --> 14:54.419
Oh.

14:54.809 --> 14:57.219
And your son?

14:57.349 --> 15:00.432
We don't have a son.

15:00.468 --> 15:02.738
But you are, uh...

15:02.785 --> 15:05.961
Jules du Florian,
are you not?

15:06.015 --> 15:07.648
Yes.

15:08.057 --> 15:11.280
Why, according to this baptismal
scroll, your son, Etienne,

15:11.316 --> 15:14.116
was baptized at
the Church of Holy Virgin.

15:14.822 --> 15:15.543
[CHUCKLES]

15:15.579 --> 15:18.702
I don't know why Father Valentin
would make that up.

15:18.738 --> 15:21.038
Yeah.
Yes, of course.

15:21.123 --> 15:25.413
We had a son, um,
but he passed away.

15:26.686 --> 15:30.029
He caught a fever
two days after his birth.

15:30.167 --> 15:32.651
Never even made it
through the night.

15:32.715 --> 15:34.764
I'm sorry for your loss.

15:35.090 --> 15:38.975
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

15:39.011 --> 15:43.063
♪♪

15:43.099 --> 15:44.898
[FLOORBOARDS CREAK]

15:44.934 --> 15:50.738
♪♪

15:50.774 --> 15:56.578
♪♪

15:56.829 --> 15:57.566
Forgive me.

15:57.602 --> 16:01.371
I... neglected to offer
my sincerest condolences.

16:01.407 --> 16:03.957
Please, allow my men and I

16:03.993 --> 16:08.128
to say a prayer on behalf
of you and your wife.

16:08.164 --> 16:09.589
Most kind of you.

16:09.837 --> 16:14.890
♪♪

16:15.128 --> 16:16.922
Where is your son
buried?

16:21.441 --> 16:24.319
Behind the Church
of the Holy Virgin.

16:27.440 --> 16:30.783
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

16:30.819 --> 16:37.624
♪♪

16:37.660 --> 16:39.376
[SWORD SCRAPES]

16:39.412 --> 16:44.549
♪♪

16:44.585 --> 16:49.679
♪♪

16:49.715 --> 16:53.220
[POT CLANKING]

16:56.681 --> 16:58.939
[BABY CRYING]

16:59.226 --> 17:05.238
♪♪

17:05.273 --> 17:11.365
Jules, thou shalt not
bear false witness.

17:14.396 --> 17:16.084
[POT CLATTERS]

17:16.119 --> 17:17.294
[GROANS]

17:17.329 --> 17:20.005
[BODY THUDS]

17:20.040 --> 17:22.257
[BABY CRYING]

17:22.292 --> 17:26.867
♪♪

17:26.960 --> 17:28.801
[CRYING]

17:28.884 --> 17:35.352
♪♪

17:35.446 --> 17:38.609
[SCREAMING]

17:39.011 --> 17:41.363
Shh, shh, shh,
shh, shh, shh.

17:41.399 --> 17:43.281
No!

17:43.317 --> 17:45.534
Take my life instead.

17:45.711 --> 17:48.886
Have mercy.
Please, have mercy on my son.

17:48.922 --> 17:51.221
I would.

17:51.618 --> 17:52.917
[CLICKS TONGUE]

17:52.953 --> 17:54.967
If he was not born
when he was.

17:55.003 --> 17:59.216
No, no, no, no!
[SCREAMING, CRYING]

18:04.918 --> 18:07.755
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

18:19.774 --> 18:20.837
[GRUNTING]

18:20.873 --> 18:23.743
Ohh, fuck!
[GRUNTS]

18:23.779 --> 18:25.745
Louis, it's okay.
It's okay.

18:25.781 --> 18:27.658
It's okay, my love.

18:28.032 --> 18:28.782
Fuck.

18:29.369 --> 18:30.116
[CLATTERING]

18:30.152 --> 18:31.910
It's all right,
my love.

18:31.946 --> 18:33.459
It's all right,
my love.

18:33.495 --> 18:35.086
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

18:35.122 --> 18:37.217
You've suffered
a-a terrible loss

18:37.253 --> 18:38.315
with the death
of your mother.

18:38.351 --> 18:39.750
You're still grieving.

18:42.462 --> 18:45.132
In time,
your heart will heal,

18:45.168 --> 18:49.339
and we will have a son who will
one day be the king of France.

18:52.061 --> 18:53.804
Swords, shields,
and helmets!

18:53.840 --> 18:56.598
[HORSE NEIGHS]

18:56.873 --> 18:58.130
Like this.

18:58.182 --> 18:59.940
A time will come

19:00.003 --> 19:02.849
when you will need both hands
to fight.

19:02.919 --> 19:05.580
You will not be able
to hold the reins.

19:05.649 --> 19:10.209
The Templar Cavalry led the army
of Richard the Lionhearted.

19:10.331 --> 19:12.565
This is in the Templar blood.

19:12.685 --> 19:16.653
This is who we are,
who you must become.

19:16.858 --> 19:21.683
Landry, around the enemy and
back with weapons at the ready.

19:21.719 --> 19:25.615
♪♪

19:25.701 --> 19:27.453
Hyah!
[HORSE SNORTS]

19:27.559 --> 19:31.784
♪♪

19:31.856 --> 19:33.238
[HORSE NEIGHS]

19:33.400 --> 19:38.834
♪♪

19:38.889 --> 19:41.337
Kelton, you're next.

19:41.450 --> 19:43.083
[HORSE SNORTS]

19:43.119 --> 19:44.317
What are you waiting for?!

19:44.353 --> 19:46.469
We're preparing to ride upon
the Luciferians

19:46.505 --> 19:48.900
and annihilate them
in God's holy name.

19:48.987 --> 19:50.203
Ride!

19:50.294 --> 19:52.296
[HORSE GRUNTING]

19:54.707 --> 19:56.500
[HORSE NEIGHS]

19:58.163 --> 19:59.879
[GRUNTS]

20:00.046 --> 20:01.103
[SIGHS]

20:01.139 --> 20:02.608
[HORSE GRUNTS]

20:02.644 --> 20:07.047
♪♪

20:07.127 --> 20:09.760
- Initiate Master, a word?
- What?

20:09.851 --> 20:11.029
- Speak.
- [SIGHS]

20:11.100 --> 20:14.109
With respect,
my fellow Initiates,

20:14.404 --> 20:17.496
they're not ready
to face the Luciferians.

20:17.647 --> 20:20.767
They were knights before
they entered our house.

20:20.803 --> 20:23.978
Knights
do not equal Templars.

20:24.248 --> 20:27.473
The worth of a man,
knight or Templar,

20:27.509 --> 20:30.101
is proven
in the theatre of war.

20:30.422 --> 20:33.681
The Luciferians count
battle-hardened warriors

20:33.717 --> 20:35.349
amongst their number,

20:35.463 --> 20:37.914
with real weapons
at their disposal.

20:37.961 --> 20:41.073
God demands
we defend His principles,

20:41.126 --> 20:44.219
training completed or not.

20:44.532 --> 20:47.326
Line up for combat!

20:47.687 --> 20:53.528
Any man who dies defending
God's will dies a noble death.

20:54.280 --> 20:57.288
Never forget that.

20:57.669 --> 21:01.876
Now you will engage the enemy
and cut him down!

21:01.912 --> 21:04.420
Permission,
Initiate Master.

21:04.873 --> 21:06.948
I would like to see
how unstoppable

21:06.984 --> 21:09.242
my fellow
Initiate Brothers are

21:09.424 --> 21:11.766
by training on me.

21:11.802 --> 21:16.604
If you wish to demonstrate
how to die, be my guest.

21:16.640 --> 21:20.399
But I would see you
off your horse.

21:20.561 --> 21:26.366
♪♪

21:26.402 --> 21:32.081
♪♪

21:32.117 --> 21:33.374
Attack!

21:33.410 --> 21:35.834
[HORSE NEIGHS]

21:35.870 --> 21:39.254
[BOTH GRUNTING]

21:39.499 --> 21:40.507
Attack!

21:40.543 --> 21:42.217
[HORSE NEIGHS]

21:42.253 --> 21:44.530
[GRUNTS]

21:44.593 --> 21:46.054
Attack!

21:46.090 --> 21:53.938
♪♪

21:54.204 --> 21:56.524
They're not ready
to face the Luciferians.

21:56.595 --> 21:59.076
I find it interesting
that you would choose

21:59.123 --> 22:01.214
to take on the role
of the enemy.

22:01.296 --> 22:02.810
If I have to
become the enemy

22:02.861 --> 22:04.828
to prove that my Initiate
Brothers aren't ready,

22:04.864 --> 22:07.158
then that is a role that
I'll take on every time.

22:08.923 --> 22:11.473
I suggest
you do the same.

22:11.509 --> 22:14.764
♪♪

22:18.705 --> 22:20.165
[METAL CLANKING]

22:24.095 --> 22:25.894
Aah! Aah!

22:27.297 --> 22:28.924
[SWORD CLATTERS]

22:32.391 --> 22:35.284
Every day that Landry's child
draws breath

22:35.320 --> 22:37.745
is an affront to us.

22:37.781 --> 22:39.414
I would see
the task completed.

22:39.490 --> 22:42.624
It will be, Father.
I promise you.

22:42.676 --> 22:43.802
Good.

22:47.679 --> 22:49.896
How is Margaret?

22:50.304 --> 22:53.380
I pray the palace
is suitable for her.

22:53.416 --> 22:56.675
She wishes Mother
was still here, of course.

22:57.010 --> 23:01.263
Do you feel
you can trust her?

23:01.492 --> 23:02.856
Of course.

23:03.306 --> 23:05.161
She's my wife.

23:05.595 --> 23:09.147
Yet she is still
a woman.

23:09.183 --> 23:12.067
Still capable of...

23:12.302 --> 23:14.747
betraying
her husband's trust.

23:14.783 --> 23:16.660
Margaret is not Mother.

23:19.490 --> 23:22.411
Well,
perhaps you're right.

23:22.678 --> 23:25.032
Your mother did
give me children.

23:25.224 --> 23:28.941
No, do not blame Margaret
for my lack of an heir.

23:29.230 --> 23:31.774
You dispatched me
to the south,

23:31.852 --> 23:34.549
and your kingdom has expanded
because of it.

23:34.619 --> 23:37.616
Would you prefer it remain
controlled by barbarians?

23:37.652 --> 23:41.954
France must never be left
with an open throne.

23:42.345 --> 23:44.433
You're here now.

23:44.469 --> 23:48.563
See that your wife provides you
with an heir...

23:48.680 --> 23:51.021
or find someone else
who can.

23:51.057 --> 23:59.849
♪♪

23:59.885 --> 24:02.143
[LIQUID SPLASHING]

24:02.659 --> 24:10.048
♪♪

24:10.084 --> 24:17.432
♪♪

24:17.468 --> 24:24.857
♪♪

24:25.025 --> 24:26.485
It's ready.

24:27.090 --> 24:29.348
Give me all of it.

24:29.775 --> 24:32.615
I've never administered
that much.

24:32.651 --> 24:34.170
I don't know
what it will do.

24:34.206 --> 24:35.947
The Persian poppy
could kill you.

24:35.983 --> 24:37.365
I said all of it.

24:37.657 --> 24:45.255
♪♪

24:45.291 --> 24:47.341
[LIQUID POURING]

24:47.377 --> 24:54.640
♪♪

24:54.676 --> 25:01.940
♪♪

25:02.140 --> 25:03.692
To bite down.

25:03.728 --> 25:12.619
♪♪

25:12.655 --> 25:14.954
[GRUNTING]

25:14.990 --> 25:19.543
♪♪

25:19.579 --> 25:21.962
[GASPING]

25:21.998 --> 25:29.054
♪♪

25:29.090 --> 25:30.925
[CHUCKLING]

25:32.525 --> 25:34.906
That was incredible.

25:34.984 --> 25:37.379
You ride as if you were born
in the saddle.

25:37.415 --> 25:38.826
Never mind that.

25:38.865 --> 25:41.197
Landry, do you think I should
carry a typical long sword,

25:41.233 --> 25:44.412
or would I fare far better
with an axe, like Talus?

25:44.545 --> 25:46.992
Do you have any tricks I could
use to master the horse?

25:47.042 --> 25:48.418
Or at least
not fall off?

25:49.443 --> 25:52.490
I hope to be
a righteous soldier,

25:52.526 --> 25:55.146
like those who fought
in the Holy Land,

25:55.197 --> 25:58.921
in Jerusalem,
in Acre.

25:59.009 --> 26:00.933
Like Landry.

26:01.251 --> 26:03.801
[FOOTSTEPS]

26:03.837 --> 26:13.354
♪♪

26:13.390 --> 26:22.666
♪♪

26:22.738 --> 26:24.323
[SIGHS]

26:26.376 --> 26:31.095
De Molay has declared war
with the Luciferians.

26:31.419 --> 26:32.409
It's only a matter of time

26:32.445 --> 26:34.587
before our scouts
find their camp.

26:36.522 --> 26:40.114
You've borne witness
to their kind.

26:40.174 --> 26:43.059
They are brutal pagans
who worship hell

26:43.134 --> 26:47.019
and feast
on blood and flesh.

26:47.690 --> 26:49.685
You will join
the Templar Knights

26:49.721 --> 26:51.479
in bringing honor
to this house

26:51.562 --> 26:55.697
and avenging your fallen
brothers in God's holy name.

26:56.063 --> 27:05.312
♪♪

27:05.348 --> 27:08.240
I'll never master the horse
in time.

27:08.291 --> 27:12.421
I don't want to end up
like Raynald and Quentin.

27:14.700 --> 27:17.334
Please, Landry...

27:17.504 --> 27:19.477
just tell us
what to do.

27:19.557 --> 27:20.732
[SIGHS]

27:20.924 --> 27:29.439
♪♪

27:29.588 --> 27:32.275
You're grown men.

27:32.428 --> 27:35.015
Never look to another man
for guidance.

27:37.465 --> 27:40.326
But look deeply
inside yourself instead.

27:40.362 --> 27:49.345
♪♪

28:06.101 --> 28:09.068
PRINCE LOUIS: Gawain.

28:09.205 --> 28:11.082
Thank you for coming.

28:12.008 --> 28:13.844
GAWAIN:
Did I have a choice?

28:15.367 --> 28:16.952
I suppose not.

28:21.427 --> 28:25.250
Quite an impressive structure,
wouldn't you say?

28:25.286 --> 28:26.871
It's just a building.

28:28.872 --> 28:32.341
This place is much more to you
than that.

28:32.589 --> 28:35.547
This was your home,

28:35.635 --> 28:40.186
where you broke bread
with your Templar brothers...

28:40.385 --> 28:42.055
with Landry.

28:43.734 --> 28:46.534
You still hate the man.

28:46.594 --> 28:48.012
I hate them all.

28:50.233 --> 28:51.502
Good.

28:51.538 --> 28:53.754
Come. Join me.

28:54.155 --> 28:59.667
♪♪

28:59.703 --> 29:05.256
♪♪

29:05.334 --> 29:06.722
Do you feel like
a fallen angel

29:06.758 --> 29:09.892
who's just walked through
the gates of heaven?

29:10.277 --> 29:11.909
I feel nothing.

29:11.945 --> 29:13.704
What do you want?

29:13.771 --> 29:15.481
What room was this?

29:17.579 --> 29:19.577
The Master's chamber.

29:19.684 --> 29:22.108
And it is again.

29:22.499 --> 29:25.276
I heard rumor that you were the
best swordsman in the Templars.

29:25.339 --> 29:27.549
I'm the best swordsman
in all of France.

29:31.071 --> 29:33.580
And your heart?

29:33.616 --> 29:35.981
Where do you place
your faith now, Templar?

29:36.044 --> 29:38.308
I'm no longer
a Templar.

29:38.387 --> 29:42.814
And any faith I have left,
I place in steel.

29:43.124 --> 29:46.216
[LAUGHS]

29:46.508 --> 29:48.175
My great-grandfather,
King Louis,

29:48.211 --> 29:50.427
was a crusader
in the Holy Land.

29:51.074 --> 29:53.448
Tales of his glory

29:53.484 --> 29:57.870
set my young mind ablaze
with thoughts of war.

29:58.291 --> 30:00.739
So enamored was I
by these stories

30:00.775 --> 30:04.828
that I even considered joining
the Templar Order.

30:05.277 --> 30:07.326
You know why I didn't?

30:07.685 --> 30:09.645
I assume
the vow of celibacy.

30:09.681 --> 30:11.313
The philosophy.

30:11.349 --> 30:14.651
Professed holy men engaged
in all that killing.

30:14.722 --> 30:19.121
You don't strike me as a man
who has a problem with killing.

30:19.186 --> 30:22.778
I don't profess
to be a man of God.

30:22.962 --> 30:25.022
Yet the Templars do,
and you once did.

30:25.058 --> 30:26.941
A man of God
is a fallacy.

30:27.242 --> 30:30.025
A term men use to excuse
their heinous acts.

30:30.061 --> 30:33.653
I've since learned
the truth.

30:33.827 --> 30:36.461
I am just a man,
like any other.

30:36.646 --> 30:39.047
And if God
truly does exist,

30:39.083 --> 30:42.301
He has turned a blind eye
to all of us.

30:42.715 --> 30:44.383
Why have you
called me here?

30:46.012 --> 30:47.604
[SWORD UNSHEATHES]

30:47.757 --> 30:52.017
♪♪

30:52.163 --> 30:56.131
You once swore loyalty
to the Templars.

30:56.233 --> 30:59.886
How can I trust you'll be loyal
to my father and I?

30:59.922 --> 31:05.308
♪♪

31:05.344 --> 31:10.689
♪♪

31:10.835 --> 31:12.608
Will a blood oath do?

31:12.644 --> 31:20.742
♪♪

31:20.778 --> 31:28.912
♪♪

31:34.711 --> 31:41.182
♪♪

31:41.218 --> 31:47.690
♪♪

31:47.850 --> 31:49.692
Landry.

31:49.728 --> 31:51.601
You should be
in the barracks, man.

31:51.730 --> 31:54.281
Talus will kill you if he
sees you here after hours.

31:54.607 --> 31:55.735
Let him.

31:57.092 --> 31:58.850
You heard the news?

31:59.113 --> 32:02.330
We ride out
after morning prayers.

32:02.366 --> 32:04.545
We've located
the Luciferians' camp.

32:04.632 --> 32:06.736
It's just half a day's ride
from here.

32:06.772 --> 32:09.275
Those heretics will pay
for their depravity.

32:11.621 --> 32:13.289
Landry, what's wrong?

32:15.471 --> 32:18.559
I just never got the chance
to properly say thank you...

32:20.451 --> 32:25.379
...for taking care of Eve,
helping me return.

32:25.669 --> 32:27.651
You've always
believed in me.

32:27.687 --> 32:32.823
♪♪

32:32.958 --> 32:35.243
Well,
what's prompting this?

32:35.390 --> 32:36.437
I just want you to know

32:36.473 --> 32:39.148
how much I value everything
you've ever done for me.

32:39.492 --> 32:46.964
♪♪

32:47.000 --> 32:48.340
[CHUCKLES]

32:48.376 --> 32:52.096
♪♪

32:52.143 --> 32:54.777
It has been my honor
to call you my brother.

32:55.009 --> 33:04.311
♪♪

